      "content": "but \"small moments of meaning\" feel like such a joke when the scale of the collapse is so huge. it's like trying to put a bandaid on a sinking ship. how am i supposed to care about a career or a life when the very foundation of everything is dying? it just feels like we're all just delaying the inevitable, and honestly, it feels more exhausting than meaningful.",
